					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/tunedtoadeadchannel" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(304457); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=304457&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610162218" alt="tunedtoadeadchannel" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=304457)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/tunedtoadeadchannel" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(304457); return false;" >tunedtoadeadchannel</a></span> <span class="odate time_1270761760 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">08 Apr 2010 21:22</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-747011">
									

<p>While I like the effort, I do think that this edit lacks a lot of the clarity of the previous version, particularly with regard to staff descriptions.</p>
<p>Bright's versions, while snarky, were informative, whereas the haikus, while cute, are not at all helpful to new users looking to find out, for example, which staff member to pester if someone is making unauthorised edits, or which to ask for formatting help. I also think that the little comments various staff members had made gave useful insight to their personalities and pressed home the fact that yes, there are in fact real people behind characters like gears and clef, and am sorry to see them removed.</p>

							</div>

								
