					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/bland" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(663362); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=663362&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610162218" alt="Bland" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=663362)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/bland" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(663362); return false;" >Bland</a></span> <span class="odate time_1314670115 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">30 Aug 2011 02:08</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-1244188">
									

<p>I think everyone can agree that there are a LOT of ways to contribute: writing, editing, fodder images, voting, commenting, chat, projects, scripting, funding, etc. There's a lot of things you can do, and they can all help a community like this.</p>
<p>I think if you join something <em>knowing</em> you're not going to do ANYTHING, though, it's rather pointless, which speaks to your own character.</p>
<p>I'm not sure I agree with the phrasing, however. You can want to join something, but not know <strong>how</strong> you can best contribute before you get into it.</p>

							</div>

								
					
